Landon Carnie and his twin sister Lorie were found huddled together as 17-month-old twins were taken to their adoptive parents in Vietnam .
The first flight of Operation Babylift - an evacuation of vulnerable Vietnamese orphans and children before the Fall of Saigon - crashed and broke up killing 78 children and 50 adults on April 4, 1975 .
Now 41, Landon has visited the crash site and is thought to be the first child survivor to return to Vietnam .